    <etym xml:lang="ru">Может быть, из *%ibælǧyl%i-%id%i с перебоем задненебный → губной, как в
        ʒuǧutur → ʒæbodur [см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ʒæbīdyr"/>] %iʒæbodur%i ‘тур’, и
        диссимиляцией плавных (%ibælvyld%i → %ibælvyrd%i). Связывается с <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                ><lang/><w>bilgi</w><gloss><q>знание</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="trk"><w>bilgili</w><gloss><q>знающий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="trk"><w>bilgilik</w><gloss><q>знак</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="trk"><w/><gloss><q>примета</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Слова эти проникли в ряд
        кавказских языков: <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"
                ><lang/><w>bergələ</w><gloss><q>метка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang=""><lang/><w>bilgalo</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""
                    ><w>belgalo</w><gloss><q>признак</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""
                ><w>bilggal</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""
                    ><w>belgala</w><gloss><q>определенно</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang=""><w/><gloss><q>наверное</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Значительность происшедших
        на осетинской почве звуковых изменений заставляет относить это слово к весьма ранним
        осетино(алано)-тюркским сношениям. В новое время слово снова усвоено в дигорский в форме
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bergelli"/> ‘определенно’, ‘несомненно’.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Maybe, it is derived from *%ibælǧyl%i-%id%i with the alternation velar →
        labial, like in %iʒuǧutur%i → %iʒæbodur%i [see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ʒæbīdyr"/>]
        ‘wild ox’, and the dissimilation of glides (%ibælvyld%i → %ibælvyrd%i). The word is
        connected with <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
            ><lang/><w>bilgi</w><gloss><q>knowledge</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                ><w>bilgili</w><gloss><q>knowing</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                ><w>bilgilik</w><gloss><q>sign</q></gloss></mentioned>, . These words were adopted
        by a number of Caucasian languages: <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"
                    ><lang/><w>bergələ</w><gloss><q>sign</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang=""><lang/><w>bilgalo</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""
                    ><w>belgalo</w><gloss><q>feature</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""
                ><w>bilggal</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""
                    ><w>belgala</w><gloss><q>definitely</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang=""><w/><gloss><q>probably</q></gloss></mentioned>, . The importance of the
        phonetical changes which took place in Ossetic makes us refer this word to quite early
        Ossetic(Alan)-Turkic relations. In the modern times the word was borrowed again in Digor:
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bergelli"/> ‘definitely’, ‘undoubtely’.</etym>
